on the National Precrime Initiative.

16:05.646 --> 16:08.846
What's the matter? Can't sleep?

16:14.197 --> 16:16.997
- Just need a little clarity.
- True that.

16:17.658 --> 16:22.258
You want the customary clarity or
the new and improved kind of clarity?

16:22.998 --> 16:24.278
Give me the new stuff.

16:24.916 --> 16:29.956
New and improved clarity.
Clarity, clarity. Yes, indeed.

16:30.714 --> 16:32.034
Come on. Come on.

16:32.299 --> 16:35.539
Don't bust my balls. You've only given
me four, and some of these are duds.

16:36.136 --> 16:37.616
Sweet dreams, chief.

16:40.682 --> 16:43.082
Don't worry.
Your secret's safe with me.

16:43.352 --> 16:45.672
I could use a little juice on my side.

16:45.939 --> 16:48.139
What do you think you know?

16:48.399 --> 16:51.039
It's like my daddy used to say:

16:51.819 --> 16:54.739
"In the land of the blind...

16:55.949 --> 17:00.149
...the one-eyed man is king. "

17:21.474 --> 17:22.795
I'm home.

17:31.402 --> 17:32.402
Overhead.

18:29.213 --> 18:30.213
Wall screen.

18:36.971 --> 18:39.211
- Sean.
- Hi, Daddy.

18:39.849 --> 18:42.049
Can you teach me how to run faster?

18:42.310 --> 18:47.150
Because all the kids in my class
run faster than me.

18:47.774 --> 18:48.854
That's good.

18:49.109 --> 18:51.269
Keep your knees up.

18:52.112 --> 18:55.032
Like that. Like that.
High. High. Like that.

18:55.699 --> 18:58.859
- See, you're a natural runner.
- Gotta keep running.

18:59.202 --> 19:01.962
Yeah. Gotta keep running.

19:02.832 --> 19:04.352
Gotta keep running.

19:05.376 --> 19:09.536
- Will I be as fast as you someday?
- Oh, I think you'll beat me someday.

19:10.089 --> 19:13.489
- You're gonna beat everybody.
- I think you'll beat everyone someday.

19:13.802 --> 19:16.962
- I gotta go. Bye.
- No, no, no. Wait, wait.

19:17.263 --> 19:19.943
- You gotta give me a kiss.
- Not on the lips.

19:20.642 --> 19:23.722
Only Mommy kisses me on the lips.

19:24.020 --> 19:25.460
Yeah, all right. All right.

19:26.106 --> 19:27.426
I love you.

19:28.025 --> 19:31.265
- I love you, Sean.
- I love you, Daddy.

20:06.523 --> 20:08.723
Reminds me of Rosarito Beach.

20:10.486 --> 20:11.726
Remember?

20:12.780 --> 20:15.140
We had 20 dollars and...

20:15.825 --> 20:19.985
Waiting in that van so the sun
would shine on our vacation.

20:22.498 --> 20:26.418
John. John. John,
put the camera down.

20:26.753 --> 20:31.713
Look, I'm all ready for bed.
What is this? No. Put it away.

20:32.092 --> 20:34.452
It's time to put the camera
to sleep...

20:34.720 --> 20:37.920
...and time to come
and take care of your wife.

20:40.517 --> 20:45.917
Why don 't you put the camera down
and come and watch the rain with me?

20:46.648 --> 20:50.248
No? I promise I'll make it
a memorable moment.

20:54.448 --> 20:57.808
Put the camera down
or you're not getting anything tonight.

21:39.538 --> 21:42.818
A gentleman at Justice
wants to take this away from us.

21:43.124 --> 21:45.804
In a week, people will vote
on whether or not...

21:46.086 --> 21:49.286
...what we've been doing has been
a noble-minded enterprise...

21:49.589 --> 21:52.829
...or a chance to change the way
this country fights crime.

21:53.218 --> 21:54.458
John...

21:55.096 --> 21:59.296
...watch this Danny Witwer,
the observer from Justice.

21:59.642 --> 22:02.442
- I met him yesterday.
- Let him look around.

22:02.728 --> 22:04.928
Answer his questions,
but watch him.

22:05.189 --> 22:07.909
If there's any problem,
make sure we know about it.

22:08.818 --> 22:12.378
When the Pre-Cogs declare a killer,
their name is embedded in the wood.

22:12.697 --> 22:17.177
Since the shape and grain of each piece
is unique, they're impossible to forge.

22:17.535 --> 22:21.135
You understand the legalistic
drawback to Precrime methodology.

22:21.456 --> 22:24.096
- Here we go again.
- I'm not with the ACLU on this...

22:24.376 --> 22:26.936
...but we arrest individuals
who've broken no law.

22:27.212 --> 22:29.772
- They will.
- The commission is metaphysics.

22:30.048 --> 22:32.688
The Pre-Cogs see the future,
and they're never wrong.

22:32.968 --> 22:34.688
But it's not the future if you stop it.

22:34.929 --> 22:38.249
- Isn't that a fundamental paradox?
- Yes.

22:38.557 --> 22:42.357
You're talking about predetermination,
which happens all the time.

22:45.440 --> 22:47.840
- Why'd you catch that?
- It was gonna fall.

22:48.109 --> 22:49.309
You're certain?

22:49.569 --> 22:51.889
But it didn't fall. You caught it.

22:53.574 --> 22:56.774
Preventing it doesn't change
the fact that it was going to happen.

22:57.077 --> 22:59.397
You ever get any false positives?

22:59.663 --> 23:04.503
Someone intends to kill, but doesn't.
How do the Pre-Cogs tell the difference?

23:04.876 --> 23:08.596
They don't see what you intend to do,
only what you will do.

23:08.923 --> 23:11.763
Why can't they see
rapes, assaults, suicides?

23:12.051 --> 23:14.011
Because of the nature of murder.

23:14.261 --> 23:17.501
Nothing's more destructive to the
metaphysical fabric that binds us...

23:17.807 --> 23:21.687
...than the untimely murder of a human.
- That wasn't Walt Whitman.

23:22.020 --> 23:26.580
Iris Hineman. She developed Pre-Cogs,
designed the system and the interface.

23:26.941 --> 23:29.741
Speaking of interfacing,
I'd love to say hello.

23:30.028 --> 23:33.308
- To Hineman?
- To them.

23:34.074 --> 23:38.394
- Cops aren't allowed inside the temple.
- You've never been inside?

23:38.745 --> 23:42.025
We keep strict separation so that
no one can be accused of tampering.

23:42.333 --> 23:46.413
- I'll be the first one to go in then?
- Maybe you didn't hear me.

23:46.796 --> 23:50.476
- If it's a question of authority...
- There is no question.

23:50.799 --> 23:52.559
You don't have any.

23:53.010 --> 23:56.010
I have a warrant in my pocket
that says different.

24:07.692 --> 24:10.612
- Show it to me.
- Sure.

24:15.909 --> 24:18.629
This investigation of Precrime
and its personnel is conducted...

24:18.912 --> 24:23.352
...under the direct supervision and
permission from the attorney general.

24:23.917 --> 24:25.917
I'm here as his representative...

24:26.170 --> 24:30.090
...which means you're now operating
under my supervision.

24:34.637 --> 24:37.837
Seems you've been left
out of the loop.

24:47.526 --> 24:50.486
All right, we're ready. Let's go.

24:56.535 --> 25:00.455
- Hold it right there. Hold on.
- Not cleared for access.

25:02.041 --> 25:04.401
Eye-dent: John Anderton. Approved.

25:11.843 --> 25:13.683
- Wally.
- No, no, no, no.

25:13.928 --> 25:17.128
Danny Witwer from Justice.
We're to give him the run of the farm.

25:17.432 --> 25:19.952
- I can't touch you.
- Don't touch anything.

25:20.226 --> 25:23.386
- You can't be in here.
- Just answer his questions.

25:23.689 --> 25:26.169
- Tell me how...
- They're sleeping.

25:26.442 --> 25:29.282
Sorry. Tell me how all this works.

25:30.571 --> 25:33.331
The photon milk acts as both a
nutrient supply and conductor.

25:33.616 --> 25:37.736
It enhances the images they receive.
We call the female Agatha.

25:38.078 --> 25:42.878
The twins are Arthur and Dashiell.
We scan by way of optical tomography.

25:43.251 --> 25:46.011
White-light pinpoints pulse
along the length of the headgear...

25:46.295 --> 25:49.295
...and are reread after absorption
through their brain tissue.

25:50.217 --> 25:52.977
In other words, we see what they see.

25:54.512 --> 25:57.912
They don't feel pain. We keep
their heads stocked with dopamine.

25:58.225 --> 26:01.585
Plus, we maintain careful control
over their serotonin levels.

26:02.103 --> 26:04.783
Don't want them to drift off
into too deep a sleep.

26:05.065 --> 26:09.545
- They can't be kept too awake either.
- Don't think of them as human.

26:10.529 --> 26:13.449
No. They're much more than that.

26:15.910 --> 26:18.830
Science has stolen
most of our miracles.

26:20.707 --> 26:24.627
In a way, they give us hope,
hope of the existence of the divine.

26:24.962 --> 26:28.642
It's interesting that some people
have begun to deify the Pre-Cogs.

26:28.965 --> 26:31.125
Pre-Cogs are pattern-recognition filters.
That's all.

26:31.385 --> 26:34.345
- Yet you call this room the "temple. "
- A nickname.

26:34.638 --> 26:36.718
The oracle isn't where
the power is, anyway.

26:36.974 --> 26:41.454
The power is with the priests,
even if they had to invent the oracle.

26:43.147 --> 26:46.027
You guys are nodding like you know
what he's talking about.

26:46.567 --> 26:50.607
Well, come on, chief. The way we work,
changing destiny and all...

26:50.946 --> 26:52.946
...we're more like clergy than cops.

26:53.199 --> 26:54.759
- Jad.
- Yeah?

26:55.201 --> 26:58.441
Go to work. All of you.

27:06.671 --> 27:08.751
Sorry. Old habit.

27:09.007 --> 27:12.527
I spent three years at Fuller Seminary
before I became a cop.

27:12.845 --> 27:15.965
- My father was proud.
- What does he think of your work?

27:16.265 --> 27:20.785
I don't know. He was shot and killed
when I was 15 at our church in Dublin.

27:21.145 --> 27:23.945
I know what it's like
to lose someone close.

27:24.231 --> 27:26.391
Nothing's like the loss of a child.

27:26.651 --> 27:30.731
I don't have any children, so I can
only imagine what that was like.

27:31.072 --> 27:34.592
To lose your son
in such a public place like that...

27:34.909 --> 27:37.989
Now we can make sure that
kind of thing doesn't happen to anyone.

27:38.288 --> 27:41.888
- Tell me what it is you're looking for.
- Flaws.

27:42.375 --> 27:44.975
There hasn't been a murder
in six years. This system is...

27:45.254 --> 27:49.694
Perfect. I agree.
If there's a flaw, it's human.

27:50.342 --> 27:52.302
It always is.

27:53.220 --> 27:55.100
John.

28:37.767 --> 28:38.847
Wally.

28:44.774 --> 28:48.614
Can you see?

29:20.812 --> 29:24.292
What happened? Her ACTH levels
just shot through the roof!

29:24.607 --> 29:26.487
- What'd you do?
- She grabbed me.

29:26.735 --> 29:30.415
Impossible. They're not aware of us.
In the milk, all they see is the future.

29:30.739 --> 29:34.619
- She looked straight at me.
- It could have been a nightmare.

29:34.951 --> 29:38.071
- She spoke to me.
- To you?

29:38.372 --> 29:40.132
What'd she say?

29:40.373 --> 29:42.773
"Can you see?"

30:02.689 --> 30:04.209
You the sentry?

30:05.024 --> 30:07.664
Yes, sir, I'm Gideon.

30:07.944 --> 30:09.944
You're Chief Anderton.

30:10.781 --> 30:13.341
The music relaxes the prisoners.

30:13.617 --> 30:16.977
I don't ever see you Precops down here.
Am I in trouble?

30:17.413 --> 30:20.373
Not yet.
I'm interested in a murder.

30:20.667 --> 30:24.107
- I got plenty of those. Kill type?
- Drowning.

30:24.420 --> 30:27.220
That narrows it down.
Not too many in here for that.

30:27.507 --> 30:30.827
- Victim's Caucasian, female.
- This about the Justice Department?

30:31.135 --> 30:35.415
I'm supposed to spruce up for a tour
they got tomorrow. You like this tie?

30:35.766 --> 30:36.766
Stop.

30:40.520 --> 30:41.840
Roll back.

30:43.399 --> 30:44.639
There.

30:44.859 --> 30:50.459
She's a golden oldie. One of our first.
Probably before your time.

30:51.073 --> 30:54.993
- This is the composite of the three?
- That's right.

30:55.327 --> 30:58.247
Combined data stream
based on all three previsions.

30:58.539 --> 31:01.779
- Just show me Agatha's data stream.
- For that...

31:03.961 --> 31:05.681
...we go for a ride.

31:27.486 --> 31:29.286
My God.

31:29.655 --> 31:31.735
I'd forgotten there were so many.

31:31.991 --> 31:36.711
And to think they'd all be out there
killing people if it wasn't for you.

31:37.371 --> 31:40.171
Look at them.
Look at how peaceful they seem.

31:40.458 --> 31:44.218
But on the inside: Busy, busy, busy.

31:44.545 --> 31:48.905
Okey-pokey.
Now that is one bad man.

31:49.301 --> 31:52.661
He drowned a woman named
Anne Lively out at Roland Lake.

31:52.971 --> 31:56.651
The killer's a John Doe,
never identified.

32:12.200 --> 32:16.240
Why is he still a John Doe?
Why wasn't he ID'd from the eye scan?

32:16.579 --> 32:21.139
Those are not his eyes. He had them
swapped out to fool the scanners.

32:21.501 --> 32:25.341
You can get it done on the street
for a few thousand bucks these days.

32:25.672 --> 32:29.352
Okay, so you want
just the female prevision.

32:29.677 --> 32:31.237
That's right.

32:37.393 --> 32:40.553
We don't seem to have her data.

32:41.438 --> 32:43.078
Try again.

32:44.567 --> 32:48.047
This is odd. See?

32:48.362 --> 32:53.042
We have the two previsions. We got
what Art saw. We got what Dash saw.

32:53.410 --> 32:56.330
But Agatha's isn't here.

32:58.790 --> 33:00.270
Probably just a glitch.

33:00.500 --> 33:04.660
Tell me about the intended victim,
this Anne Lively.

33:05.213 --> 33:09.053
Looks like she's a neuroin addict,
like our John Doe here.

33:09.385 --> 33:12.225
Address history
includes the Beaton Clinic.

33:12.512 --> 33:15.592
So she cleaned up.
Where is she now?

33:17.393 --> 33:20.113
I guess glitches come in twos.

33:21.605 --> 33:26.445
You finally crawl your way out
of one hole just to fall into another.

33:31.825 --> 33:32.825
No.

33:34.244 --> 33:37.164
Can't let you take that out of here,
chief.

33:38.081 --> 33:41.721
- It's against the rules.
- Anything else against the rules?

33:47.341 --> 33:53.341
Careful, chief. You dig up the past,
all you get is dirty.

33:58.269 --> 34:01.709
The third prevision was what,
kind of fuzzy or something?

34:02.064 --> 34:06.104
No, the third prevision,
Agatha's prevision, wasn't there.

34:06.486 --> 34:11.406
That's not all. There are a dozen more
cases with missing previsions.

34:11.783 --> 34:14.902
You'd think we'd have found
the cure for the common cold.

34:15.245 --> 34:17.445
- It's stress.
- What's this?

34:17.746 --> 34:19.627
Herbal tea with honey.

34:19.917 --> 34:23.277
I hate herbal tea.
Almost as much as I hate honey.

34:23.629 --> 34:26.349
Just drink it,
before I pour it in your lap.

34:26.632 --> 34:29.391
- Can I get you anything, John?
- No, thank you.

34:29.886 --> 34:33.326
Witwer's scheduled for a tour
of Containment tomorrow.

34:33.681 --> 34:35.561
Yeah, give him a tour.

34:37.018 --> 34:39.418
- Lara called me.
- What?

34:40.147 --> 34:43.347
She's worried about you.
Quite frankly, so am I.

34:44.234 --> 34:45.514
I'm fine.

34:45.777 --> 34:49.496
I understand you've been spending
a lot of time in the Sprawl.

34:50.991 --> 34:53.871
- I go running down there.
- In the middle of the night.

34:54.661 --> 34:57.621
What if Danny Witwer
insisted on a full chem run?

34:57.956 --> 34:59.556
I'm fine.

35:01.126 --> 35:05.406
The minute Precrime goes national,
they are going to take it away.

35:05.798 --> 35:08.038
- We won't let them.
- No?

35:08.342 --> 35:12.462
How is an old man and a cop on the
whiff ever going to stop them?

35:13.348 --> 35:15.548
My father once said to me...

35:15.850 --> 35:19.850
..."You don't choose the things
you believe in. They choose you. "

35:20.188 --> 35:22.028
There's a reason you are here.

35:22.315 --> 35:27.835
Had Precrime been in place earlier,
your loss would have been prevented.

35:28.280 --> 35:29.760
Remember, the eyes...

35:32.159 --> 35:35.439
The eyes of the nation
are on us right now.

35:35.913 --> 35:38.993
I'm not the generation
anyone listens to...

35:39.333 --> 35:43.333
...but people trust you when you
speak of your belief in Precrime.

35:44.088 --> 35:48.368
They know that it's a belief born of
pain, not politics. I understood that.

35:48.718 --> 35:52.158
I may have even encouraged it
to help with the cause.

35:53.890 --> 35:57.730
But now,
your pain is hurting both of us.

36:01.899 --> 36:04.459
They're not going to take it
away from us.

36:05.569 --> 36:07.169
I won't let them.

36:37.894 --> 36:39.254
Bingo.

36:52.493 --> 36:54.253
- Hi, Daddy.
- Hey, buddy.

36:54.537 --> 36:56.377
- I made up a club.
- Yeah?

36:56.664 --> 37:00.144
- We're called the Crescos.
- The Crescos.

37:00.501 --> 37:02.901
- We made up a soccer team.
- Yeah?

37:03.213 --> 37:05.813
- We practice at school.
- With Connor?

37:06.133 --> 37:09.053
Your daddy's in a lot of trouble,
Sean.

37:34.203 --> 37:36.563
- Wait!
- No!

37:39.334 --> 37:41.934
Jad, how come you're not with
Father Witwer?

37:42.253 --> 37:47.773
We're in motion on something. We got a
white, male victim, about 5' 10", 170.

37:48.176 --> 37:50.656
He takes a round in the 10-ring
and goes out a window.

37:50.971 --> 37:52.691
- Red Ball?
- Nope. Brown Ball.

37:52.973 --> 37:54.133
It's premeditated.

37:54.391 --> 37:57.871
Amazing. There's someone within
200 miles still dumb enough to do that.

37:58.187 --> 37:59.667
The victim's name is Leo Crow.

37:59.939 --> 38:04.299
This is case number 1109. Time of
occurrence: Friday, 1506 hours.

38:04.693 --> 38:08.973
Start search for Leo Crow. Case 1109,
previsualized by the Pre-Cogs...

38:09.365 --> 38:12.525
...recorded on holosphere
by Precrime's Q-stacks.

38:12.868 --> 38:17.148
My fellow witnesses are Dr. Katherine
James and Chief Justice Frank Pollard.

38:17.540 --> 38:18.740
Good morning.

38:19.001 --> 38:21.561
Are you ready
to preview and validate 1109?

38:21.878 --> 38:24.678
- Ready when you are, John.
- Standing by.

38:30.554 --> 38:32.274
I love this part.

38:33.390 --> 38:38.190
I've got no address. No tax returns
for the last five years.

38:38.562 --> 38:41.042
Check NCIC.
Maybe he's got a number.

38:41.983 --> 38:45.583
We'll send a protection team
as soon as we lock location.

38:48.865 --> 38:51.465
It looks like federal housing.
Concrete, glass, egg crates.

38:51.743 --> 38:54.703
Ouch. About a thousand of those
in the District.

38:56.331 --> 38:58.051
Fractured images coming in.

38:58.333 --> 39:00.613
Numbers nine...

39:03.255 --> 39:04.895
Nine, six.

39:09.553 --> 39:13.393
Female, senior. She's smoking a pipe.

39:14.392 --> 39:15.632
She's laughing.

39:19.271 --> 39:21.311
Okay, now I'm inside a room.

39:22.317 --> 39:24.957
Windowpanes, aluminum extrusion.

39:25.611 --> 39:28.651
Two figures resolving in the room.

39:29.824 --> 39:31.864
- Wait!
- No...

39:35.497 --> 39:37.617
Looks like we got a third party.

39:38.584 --> 39:41.144
Wearing sunglasses,
just out the window.

39:41.962 --> 39:43.842
You're not gonna kill me.

39:46.467 --> 39:48.067
Goodbye, Crow.

39:54.058 --> 39:55.858
You're not gonna kill me.

39:56.311 --> 39:58.231
- Goodbye, Crow.
- Wait!

40:02.192 --> 40:04.232
Wait. Wait.

40:04.820 --> 40:06.660
You say something, chief?

40:06.946 --> 40:08.106
No.

40:11.660 --> 40:13.260
I'll get this one.

40:13.787 --> 40:15.747
We got time on this one, Jad.

40:15.997 --> 40:18.837
Mind getting me a piece
of cake they're eating?

40:19.168 --> 40:20.928
- I'm starving.
- Sure, chief.

40:21.170 --> 40:23.890
I think I'll get one for myself too.

40:24.173 --> 40:25.613
Take your time.

40:42.359 --> 40:45.879
Chief Anderton,
what is this that I'm seeing?

40:46.738 --> 40:48.178
I'm confused about...

41:20.148 --> 41:22.108
- Anderton, wait!
- Goodbye, Crow.

41:22.400 --> 41:23.680
Anderton, wait!

41:25.612 --> 41:27.452
Anderton, wait!

41:33.704 --> 41:37.344
I like you, chief.
You've always been nice to me.

41:39.752 --> 41:42.632
Give you two minutes
before I hit the alarm.

41:59.148 --> 42:00.508
Hold that, please.

42:01.858 --> 42:03.058
Thanks.

42:06.405 --> 42:09.925
- You're in a lot of trouble, John.
- You set me up.

42:10.284 --> 42:13.084
I'll write the paranoia off to the
whiff you've been doping on.

42:13.412 --> 42:14.612
Easy.

42:14.872 --> 42:17.032
- Easy.
- Seems I've found a flaw.

42:19.627 --> 42:20.787
What are you gonna do?

42:21.045 --> 42:23.845
Possession will cost you six months
and your badge.

42:24.132 --> 42:26.532
I guess we won't be working together
after all.

42:26.843 --> 42:30.323
Now put the gun down, John.
I don't hear a Red Ball.

42:51.911 --> 42:53.911
Lamar. Lamar.

42:56.583 --> 42:58.863
- Lamar?
- John, what is happening?

42:59.168 --> 43:01.088
It's Witwer. He set me up!

43:01.337 --> 43:02.617
Stop, just wait.

43:02.839 --> 43:05.679
- Witwer! It's Witwer.
- Who's the victim?

43:06.009 --> 43:07.569
- Somebody.
- Who?

43:07.844 --> 43:09.764
- Somebody... Leo Crow.
- Who is he?

43:10.055 --> 43:12.695
I have no idea!
I've never heard of him.

43:13.017 --> 43:15.897
But I'm supposed to kill him
in less than 36 hours.

43:16.186 --> 43:19.346
- How could Witwer have access?
- Can you fake a cerebral output?

43:19.690 --> 43:21.250
- Why would anyone want to?
- Can you?

43:21.525 --> 43:23.765
- I doubt it.
- Would Hineman know?

43:24.028 --> 43:26.028
- Now listen, come in.
- What?

43:26.322 --> 43:28.642
I'll protect you until we
get to the bottom of this.

43:28.950 --> 43:31.870
Talk to Wally. See if Witwer's gone
inside the temple again.

43:32.203 --> 43:35.523
Ask Jad for any off-hour
eye-dents into the analytical room.

43:36.416 --> 43:38.136
Who's Leo Crow?

43:38.418 --> 43:41.098
Security lockdown enabled.
Revised destination: Office.

43:41.379 --> 43:43.979
Lamar, they found me.

43:48.512 --> 43:51.592
Is there any way to override
the lockdown?

43:51.932 --> 43:53.772
- No, no, no.
- No?

43:54.059 --> 43:57.419
I'll meet you anywhere you say.
You can come to my house, John.

43:57.771 --> 44:00.251
I can't. They'll get me.
I'm not gonna get haloed.

44:00.566 --> 44:01.646
You can't run.

44:02.651 --> 44:03.851
Everybody runs.

44:50.952 --> 44:52.792
- Oh, my God!
- Hey, hey.

45:07.469 --> 45:10.029
Oh, my gosh, are you okay?

45:13.393 --> 45:15.513
I'll bring him in. Unharmed.

45:15.811 --> 45:18.371
You're not gonna do that.
I'm taking control.

45:18.648 --> 45:19.848
What?

45:20.108 --> 45:24.348
Fletcher is second in command.
It's his show to run. You can observe.

45:24.737 --> 45:27.977
- Do it. Find him.
- Yes, sir.

45:30.119 --> 45:33.599
He came to see you the other day
right before he was tagged.

45:33.955 --> 45:36.435
- What did you talk about?
- The Mets.

45:36.750 --> 45:39.470
John doesn't think they have a deep
enough pitching roster.

45:39.795 --> 45:43.515
Why are you protecting him? You knew
he was doping, yet you did nothing.

45:43.883 --> 45:47.083
- The man lost a child, for chrissake.
- Six years ago.

45:47.428 --> 45:50.348
- What did you talk about?
- None of your business.

45:50.681 --> 45:55.001
It's my business. Investigation of a
supervising officer for a capital crime...

45:55.353 --> 45:59.313
...falls under federal jurisdiction
so as to rule out any conspiracy.

45:59.691 --> 46:02.011
- He's my suspect.
- He's my subordinate.

46:02.319 --> 46:05.799
Call the attorney general. I'm sure
he'd clarify the issue for you.

46:06.156 --> 46:09.356
I don't want John Anderton hurt.

46:11.370 --> 46:13.650
I'm going to enjoy working here.

46:16.625 --> 46:18.785
A road diverges in the desert.

46:19.462 --> 46:20.742
Lexus.

46:21.004 --> 46:24.724
The road you're on, John Anderton,
is the one less-traveled.

46:25.092 --> 46:28.092
- Make sure you...
- Diamonds...

46:30.389 --> 46:32.429
Good evening, John Anderton.

46:35.729 --> 46:39.489
John Anderton! You could use
a Guinness right about now.

46:42.152 --> 46:44.792
- John Anderton...
- Escape from it all.

46:45.113 --> 46:49.593
Get away, John Anderton.
Forget your troubles.

47:06.761 --> 47:11.041
He's been eye-dented on the Metro.
The train stops at 20th and 33rd.

47:11.432 --> 47:13.152
Send units to each location.

47:13.435 --> 47:15.155
- Better make 20th.
- Have faith.

47:56.271 --> 47:57.631
Fire them up!

48:21.840 --> 48:23.760
- Hey, Fletch.
- Hey, John.

48:24.008 --> 48:26.088
- That was a rough landing.
- Yeah.

48:26.344 --> 48:28.704
- Work on that.
- It's the shit knee of mine.

48:29.014 --> 48:30.854
- Yeah.
- Don't do it.

48:31.683 --> 48:33.443
Hey, don't do this.

48:34.269 --> 48:35.469
John?

48:35.854 --> 48:37.134
Don't run.

48:37.690 --> 48:39.650
You don't have to chase me.

48:40.317 --> 48:41.917
You don't have to run.

48:42.319 --> 48:44.119
Everybody runs, Fletch.

48:44.405 --> 48:46.325
You know we'll catch you.

48:47.408 --> 48:49.048
Everybody runs.

48:51.079 --> 48:55.039
- It doesn't have to be like this, John.
- Everybody runs.

48:55.374 --> 48:57.414
Get your sick-sticks ready.

48:58.878 --> 49:00.558
Everybody runs, Fletch.

49:01.173 --> 49:03.653
Slow down, chief. Just take it easy.

49:07.763 --> 49:09.603
No sudden moves, chief.

49:10.890 --> 49:12.810
John, it's okay.

49:13.352 --> 49:15.472
- Fletch...
- Easy does it, chief.

49:44.175 --> 49:45.375
Got a grip?

49:45.594 --> 49:47.274
- Got a grip?
- Yeah.

50:16.125 --> 50:17.485
Anderton!

50:48.701 --> 50:51.301
Go away! Get out of my kitchen!

50:51.621 --> 50:54.541
Get out of my house!
Get out of my house! Go!

50:57.669 --> 51:00.069
- Get them out of here!
- Anderton, stop!

51:00.339 --> 51:02.939
Pull him off me, Fletcher.
Get him off me.

51:04.760 --> 51:07.840
Get him out of here!
What's the matter with you?!

51:13.060 --> 51:15.180
Get out of my house! Go!

51:35.835 --> 51:39.955
By mandate of the District of Columbia,
I'm placing you under arrest for...

51:40.339 --> 51:41.619
Go to sleep.

52:02.570 --> 52:04.050
You two stay with me!

56:34.981 --> 56:36.341
Dr. Hineman.

56:37.025 --> 56:40.105
You're trespassing.
I don't have visitors.

56:45.534 --> 56:48.414
That would be from the doll's eye,
the vine...

56:48.703 --> 56:51.903
...the baneberry that scratched you
during your illegal climb over my wall.

56:52.207 --> 56:55.887
It's not a true doll's eye.
It's a little hybrid I designed.

56:56.253 --> 56:59.853
Once the poison gets into your
bloodstream, you'll start to see...

57:00.216 --> 57:04.216
...the most extraordinary display
of blue objects.

57:04.553 --> 57:07.913
This just isn't your week, is it?

57:09.559 --> 57:10.999
Chief Anderton.

57:13.479 --> 57:14.999
I'm not a killer.

57:21.112 --> 57:22.512
You better drink this.

57:22.781 --> 57:26.661
Soon you won't be able to swallow,
and then you'll be totally buggered.

57:28.078 --> 57:29.278
All of it.

57:30.080 --> 57:33.360
Okay, now take a minute
to right yourself.

57:34.876 --> 57:38.316
Just what is it you think
I can do for you?

57:40.925 --> 57:45.165
You could tell me how someone
can fake a prevision.

57:45.555 --> 57:47.435
How would I know that?

57:47.891 --> 57:50.291
Because you invented Precrime.

57:52.437 --> 57:53.957
What's so funny?

57:54.522 --> 57:59.402
If the consequences of several genetic
mistakes and science gone haywire...

57:59.777 --> 58:02.537
...can be called an invention,
then I invented Precrime.

58:02.864 --> 58:04.784
- You don't seem proud.
- I'm not.

58:05.075 --> 58:08.115
I was trying to heal them,
not turn them into something else.

58:08.412 --> 58:11.092
- Heal who?
- The innocents we use to stop the guilty.

58:11.415 --> 58:14.495
You're talking about the Pre-Cogs.

58:14.836 --> 58:19.796
You think they came from a test tube?
They are merely the ones who survived.

58:20.216 --> 58:23.856
I was doing genetic research,
treating children of drug addicts.

58:24.220 --> 58:27.700
This was 10 years ago,
when neuroin first hit the streets.

58:28.058 --> 58:33.978
It was impure, not the engineered
cocktail popular among the educated.

58:35.148 --> 58:40.668
All of these kids were born with severe
brain damage. Most died before age 12.

58:41.113 --> 58:43.713
Those few who survived,
they had a gift.

58:43.991 --> 58:47.191
I call it a gift. For them,
it was more like a cosmic joke.

58:47.537 --> 58:50.177
They would wake up in the night,
curled in the corner...

58:50.497 --> 58:52.337
...screaming, clawing at the walls.

58:52.625 --> 58:56.785
Because when these children
closed their eyes at night...

58:57.129 --> 59:01.409
...they dreamt only of murder
over and over, one after the other.

59:01.760 --> 59:05.200
It didn't take for us long to realize
that the real nightmare was...

59:05.555 --> 59:10.315
...that these dreams were about to come
true, these murders were happening.

59:14.439 --> 59:16.759
You say some of the children died?

59:17.067 --> 59:20.147
So many of them.
Despite what we did for them.

59:20.487 --> 59:24.567
Or maybe because of what we
did to them. But it doesn't matter.

59:24.950 --> 59:27.630
It's a perfect system now, isn't it?

59:28.871 --> 59:30.911
I'm not going to commit murder.

59:31.207 --> 59:33.487
I've never met the man
I'm supposed to kill.

59:33.793 --> 59:37.873
And yet a chain of events has started
that will lead you to his murder.

59:38.256 --> 59:40.936
- Not if I stay away from him.
- Can you avoid a man you've never met?

59:41.259 --> 59:44.099
- You won't help?
- I can't help you. Nobody can.

59:44.430 --> 59:47.110
The Pre-Cogs are never wrong.

59:49.601 --> 59:51.641
But occasionally...

59:52.271 --> 59:54.311
...they do disagree.

59:55.899 --> 59:57.019
What?

59:57.359 --> 01:00:01.879
Most of the time, all three Pre-Cogs
will see an event in the same way...

01:00:02.239 --> 01:00:06.039
...but once in a while, one of them will
see things differently than the others.

01:00:06.369 --> 01:00:10.249
Jesus Christ.
Why didn't I know about this?

01:00:11.165 --> 01:00:14.245
Because these Minority Reports
are destroyed the instant they occur.

01:00:14.544 --> 01:00:15.664
Why?

01:00:15.879 --> 01:00:20.639
For Precrime to function, there can't
be any suggestion of fallibility.

01:00:21.009 --> 01:00:24.009
Who wants a justice system
that instills doubt?

01:00:24.305 --> 01:00:27.105
It may be reasonable,
but it's still doubt.

01:00:28.642 --> 01:00:31.362
Are you saying
I've haloed innocent people?

01:00:31.645 --> 01:00:35.245
I'm saying that every so often,
those accused of a Precrime...

01:00:35.566 --> 01:00:38.046
...just might have
an alternate future.

01:00:38.319 --> 01:00:42.079
Does Burgess know about this,
about this Minority Report?

01:00:42.448 --> 01:00:45.848
I used to joke with Lamar that
we were the parents of Precrime.

01:00:46.160 --> 01:00:50.880
Parents often see their children as they
want them to be and not as they are.

01:00:51.249 --> 01:00:56.209
Answer my question: Does Lamar
Burgess know about the Minority Report?

01:00:56.588 --> 01:00:58.188
Yes, of course, he knew.

01:00:58.423 --> 01:01:03.463
But at the time, we felt their existence
was an insignificant variable.

01:01:03.846 --> 01:01:05.726
Insignificant to you, maybe.

01:01:05.972 --> 01:01:09.612
But what about those people that
I put away with alternate futures?

01:01:09.977 --> 01:01:13.497
- My God, if the country knew...
- The system would collapse.

01:01:15.691 --> 01:01:18.211
- I believe in that system.
- Do you really?

01:01:18.486 --> 01:01:20.046
You wanna bring it down.

01:01:20.280 --> 01:01:24.040
You will bring it down
if you manage to kill your victim.

01:01:24.367 --> 01:01:29.247
That'll be the most spectacular public
display of how Precrime didn't work.

01:01:29.623 --> 01:01:32.463
- I'm not gonna kill anybody.
- Hold that thought.

01:01:32.751 --> 01:01:36.071
- Why should I trust you?
- You shouldn't trust anyone.

01:01:36.380 --> 01:01:39.500
Certainly not the attorney general,
who wants it all for himself.

01:01:39.800 --> 01:01:42.440
And not the young federal agent,
who wants your job.

01:01:42.761 --> 01:01:46.801
Not even the old man who just wants
to hang on to what he created.

01:01:47.140 --> 01:01:50.420
Don't trust anyone.
Just find the Minority Report.

01:01:52.480 --> 01:01:54.160
You said the Minority Report
is destroyed.

01:01:54.482 --> 01:01:58.042
The record is destroyed.
The original report still exists.

01:01:58.361 --> 01:02:03.401
I designed it so the report is stored
in a safe place, but not declared.

01:02:03.783 --> 01:02:05.983
What safe place is that?

01:02:06.244 --> 01:02:09.364
The safest place there is.

01:02:09.707 --> 01:02:12.547
Where is it?

01:02:14.795 --> 01:02:18.635
Inside the Pre-Cog who predicted it.

01:02:23.387 --> 01:02:27.747
All you have to do
is download it, darling.

01:02:29.518 --> 01:02:31.118
That's all, huh?

01:02:34.608 --> 01:02:37.328
Just walk into Precrime,
get into the temple...

01:02:37.610 --> 01:02:42.090
...somehow tap into these Pre-Cogs
and download this Minority Report.

01:02:42.449 --> 01:02:44.849
- If you have one.
- And then walk out.

01:02:45.118 --> 01:02:49.438
Actually, you'll have to run out.
But yes, that's what you have to do.

01:02:50.499 --> 01:02:52.459
You're insane.

01:02:53.168 --> 01:02:55.208
Or you think I am.

01:02:55.462 --> 01:03:00.462
I'll get eye-scanned a dozen times
before I get within 10 miles of Precrime.

01:03:00.843 --> 01:03:05.483
Sometimes in order to see the light,
you have to risk the dark.

01:03:05.849 --> 01:03:09.049
As a policeman...
Excuse me, as a former policeman...

01:03:09.352 --> 01:03:11.952
...I'm sure that you know
all sorts of people...

01:03:12.272 --> 01:03:15.432
...who can help you out
in this regard.

01:03:21.698 --> 01:03:24.618
It's funny how all
living organisms are alike.

01:03:24.909 --> 01:03:28.469
When the chips are down,
when the pressure is on...

01:03:28.789 --> 01:03:31.629
...every creature
on the face of the earth...

01:03:31.918 --> 01:03:35.238
...is interested in one thing
and one thing only:

01:03:36.380 --> 01:03:38.500
Its own survival.

01:03:40.218 --> 01:03:42.298
Find the Minority Report.

01:03:47.476 --> 01:03:50.116
How do I even know which one has it?

01:03:50.395 --> 01:03:53.595
It's always in the more gifted
of the three.

01:03:55.317 --> 01:03:57.157
Which one is that?

01:04:00.197 --> 01:04:01.997
The female.

01:04:05.160 --> 01:04:08.720
We've got three men in a room.
The victim is here...

01:04:09.039 --> 01:04:13.079
...John is here, and this
unidentified male, at the window.

01:04:13.419 --> 01:04:17.099
The adjacent building suggests
public housing, which means...

01:04:17.423 --> 01:04:20.143
- There's thousands like this one.
- They're everywhere.

01:04:20.427 --> 01:04:23.227
But he doesn't go there to kill Crow
for another 22 hours.

01:04:23.513 --> 01:04:25.633
This is Chief Anderton's space.

01:04:25.890 --> 01:04:27.730
- He's not here.
- He'll be back.

01:04:27.976 --> 01:04:31.576
I doubt that. I'm betting
he's somewhere in the Sprawl.

01:04:31.897 --> 01:04:35.577
He's smart enough to go
where billboards can't ID him.

01:04:35.901 --> 01:04:38.181
There's fewer consumers,
which means fewer scanners.

01:04:38.445 --> 01:04:42.525
- Why won't he just run?
- Because he thinks he's innocent.

01:04:43.951 --> 01:04:45.711
We concentrate on the Sprawl.

01:04:45.953 --> 01:04:48.873
We do fly-overs in ships,
with two spyder teams on the ground.

01:04:49.165 --> 01:04:53.325
Thermal scan the entire area. Read
anything with eyes and a heartbeat.

01:05:09.353 --> 01:05:10.593
Where is she?

01:05:29.165 --> 01:05:34.925
Started blowing buttons for no reason
whatsoever, and I knew that.

01:05:38.758 --> 01:05:40.758
This damn cold.

01:05:42.012 --> 01:05:46.092
Don't worry. I could cut open your
chest and sew a dead cat in there...

01:05:46.433 --> 01:05:50.913
...you wouldn't get an infection. Not
with the antibios I'll shoot into you.

01:05:51.271 --> 01:05:52.711
That's comforting.

01:05:52.940 --> 01:05:56.220
You do understand I can't just
give you new irises?

01:05:56.527 --> 01:05:57.927
Please, don't touch.

01:05:58.154 --> 01:06:01.954
Because the scanners would read the
new scar tissue, alarms will go off...

01:06:02.283 --> 01:06:04.763
...and large men with guns will appear.

01:06:07.329 --> 01:06:09.009
What was that?

01:06:09.248 --> 01:06:10.368
What was that?

01:06:10.583 --> 01:06:15.023
- It's anesthesia. It's all downhill...
- You always sneak up on your patients?

01:06:15.380 --> 01:06:19.340
You wouldn't break the hand
of a violinist before the concert.

01:06:19.676 --> 01:06:21.236
Please, relax.

01:06:25.849 --> 01:06:30.929
All I'm trying to tell you is that I'll
have to remove your eyes completely.

01:06:31.313 --> 01:06:32.433
I know.

01:06:33.399 --> 01:06:37.439
- I have to replace them with new ones.
- I know. But I wanna keep the old ones.

01:06:37.779 --> 01:06:41.299
- Why?
- Because my mother gave them to me.

01:06:41.616 --> 01:06:43.896
What's it to you?
You can't resell them.

01:06:44.160 --> 01:06:46.960
Whatever you say. It's your money.

01:06:54.338 --> 01:06:58.818
Let me introduce my gorgeous
assistant, Miss Van Eyck.

01:07:19.781 --> 01:07:24.021
- This is not a lot of money.
- It's all that I could safely move.

01:07:27.122 --> 01:07:28.682
Okay.

01:07:32.544 --> 01:07:35.784
- What did you give me?
- Smile medicine.

01:07:36.089 --> 01:07:38.489
Tell you what, since we go way back...

01:07:38.759 --> 01:07:42.879
...why don't I give you my old pal
discount? What do you say?

01:07:43.222 --> 01:07:45.382
You don't remember me, do you?

01:07:45.641 --> 01:07:49.001
- We know each other?
- Yes, we do.

01:07:49.395 --> 01:07:51.275
From where? D.C.?

01:07:51.523 --> 01:07:55.923
- Baltimore. The East Side.
- Baltimore? We go way back.

01:07:56.277 --> 01:08:00.157
Solomon P. Eddie, M.D.
I was a plastic surgeon.

01:08:00.490 --> 01:08:05.530
You remember? Specialized
in burn victims, mostly women.

01:08:05.913 --> 01:08:09.433
- I put you away.
- Yeah, you did.

01:08:11.376 --> 01:08:13.536
You made those tapes.

01:08:13.796 --> 01:08:16.276
They were performance pieces.

01:08:17.674 --> 01:08:21.674
- You set your patients on fire.
- I put them out.

01:08:22.013 --> 01:08:27.173
Some not as quickly as others, but
let's change the subject, shall we?

01:08:29.145 --> 01:08:34.585
The future's so much more interesting
than the past, don't you think?

01:08:37.529 --> 01:08:41.408
Miss Van Eyck.
I'm afraid she's already smitten.

01:08:42.158 --> 01:08:46.318
She only has eyes for you.

01:08:47.497 --> 01:08:51.178
I know what you're thinking, John:
How can I do what I do now?

01:08:51.502 --> 01:08:56.022
Let's say that I spent an awful lot
of time in the prison library.

01:08:56.381 --> 01:09:01.381
That was a great way to avoid the more
unpleasant aspects of prison life.

01:09:01.763 --> 01:09:05.002
Confinement was
a real education, a real...

01:09:07.268 --> 01:09:08.707
...eye-opener.

01:09:13.233 --> 01:09:16.273
For true enlightenment,
there's nothing quite like...

01:09:16.569 --> 01:09:19.810
...well, let's say, taking a shower
while this large fellow...

01:09:20.157 --> 01:09:23.517
...with an attitude you can't
knock down with a hammer...

01:09:23.827 --> 01:09:25.907
...whispers in your ear, "Oh, Nancy. "

01:09:26.162 --> 01:09:29.683
That was a lot of fun.
Thank you for putting me there...

01:09:30.000 --> 01:09:34.080
...and giving me the opportunity to
get to know myself so much better.

01:09:34.421 --> 01:09:36.782
And now to return the favor.

01:09:48.269 --> 01:09:51.229
- This your work?
- Yes.

01:09:52.024 --> 01:09:53.544
I like it.

01:09:53.776 --> 01:09:56.736
- How do you take your coffee?
- Cream and sugar.

01:09:57.029 --> 01:09:59.469
- I don't have any cream. Sorry.
- Just sugar then.

01:09:59.740 --> 01:10:02.020
- You and John ever come here?
- We used to.

01:10:02.285 --> 01:10:04.045
He's not here now, is he?

01:10:06.288 --> 01:10:08.048
I had to ask.

01:10:10.542 --> 01:10:13.382
- I don't have any sugar either.
- Thank you.

01:10:13.671 --> 01:10:16.511
- He hasn't tried to contact you?
- No.

01:10:16.800 --> 01:10:19.320
Did he ever mention the name
Leo Crow?

01:10:19.594 --> 01:10:22.354
No, but I don't talk
to John much anymore.

01:10:22.639 --> 01:10:26.079
- So you haven't seen his apartment.
- That was our apartment.

01:10:26.393 --> 01:10:29.233
Have you been there recently?
It's full of these.

01:10:29.521 --> 01:10:33.961
- How long has he been doping?
- Since right after we lost our son.

01:10:34.318 --> 01:10:39.558
- You mean after he lost your son.
- It was nobody's fault.

01:10:41.367 --> 01:10:45.367
But John was with him
at the public pool.

01:10:45.913 --> 01:10:48.393
You said in your divorce papers
that John tried to kill himself.

01:10:48.666 --> 01:10:51.866
- It wasn't a suicide attempt.
- What was it then?

01:10:52.169 --> 01:10:56.089
The FBI found something
that belonged to my son, a sandal.

01:10:56.424 --> 01:10:57.944
John was upset. He...

01:10:58.218 --> 01:11:01.058
He took out his gun
and watched home movies.

01:11:01.346 --> 01:11:05.466
- This is all in your statement.
- He shot a hole in the ceiling. So what?

01:11:05.809 --> 01:11:09.329
You lose your son,
let's see how well you handle it.

01:11:09.896 --> 01:11:14.776
Lamar thinks you left John because he
lost himself in Precrime instead of you.

01:11:15.486 --> 01:11:20.006
I left him because every time
I looked at him, I saw my son.

01:11:21.075 --> 01:11:25.355
Every time I got close to him,
I smelled my little boy.

01:11:25.705 --> 01:11:28.225
That's why I left him.

01:11:29.334 --> 01:11:31.454
And now you can leave.

01:11:33.504 --> 01:11:36.544
Don't take the bandages off
for 12 hours.

01:11:41.471 --> 01:11:45.591
If you take them off before then,
you'll go blind. Understand?

01:11:46.894 --> 01:11:50.734
In the fridge, there's milk.
Greta made you a sandwich.

01:11:51.065 --> 01:11:53.785
Make sure you drink a lot of water.

01:11:54.068 --> 01:11:55.988
How do I find the bathroom?

01:11:56.570 --> 01:11:59.970
The bathroom?
Now that's your right hand.

01:12:02.661 --> 01:12:05.181
The kitchen is your left.

01:12:07.498 --> 01:12:10.218
Don't scratch. Never scratch!

01:12:10.752 --> 01:12:15.232
Seeing as we're being pals, I'll give
you a bonus that may come in handy.

01:12:15.590 --> 01:12:19.790
This is a temporary paralytic enzyme.
You're gonna shoot this under your chin.

01:12:20.304 --> 01:12:23.544
- What is this?
- It'll turn your pretty face into mush.

01:12:23.849 --> 01:12:26.169
People won't even recognize you.

01:12:26.435 --> 01:12:30.595
In 30 minutes, it'll tighten up again.
But it'll hurt like you've never felt.

01:12:30.940 --> 01:12:34.780
I'm gonna put this in your goody-bag,
together with your...

01:12:35.153 --> 01:12:36.913
...leftovers.

01:12:38.656 --> 01:12:44.096
I'm setting up a timer. When it rings,
you can remove the bandages and leave.

01:12:44.496 --> 01:12:48.296
- But not before then, or you will...
- Go blind. I know.

01:12:48.625 --> 01:12:50.465
Don't scratch.

01:12:51.503 --> 01:12:56.063
A little something from
a mutual friend of ours.

01:13:32.963 --> 01:13:35.443
Don 't take the bandages off
for 12 hours.

01:13:36.508 --> 01:13:41.068
If you take them off before then,
you'll go blind. Understand?

01:14:01.952 --> 01:14:06.552
- 25. 16 seconds. That's a new record.
- Is that a world record?

01:14:06.915 --> 01:14:10.275
Is it a world record?
It's a personal best.

01:14:10.586 --> 01:14:13.506
- Now I wanna time you.
- You gotta be kidding.

01:14:13.798 --> 01:14:16.638
There's no way
I can beat 25. 16 seconds.

01:14:16.926 --> 01:14:19.646
How long can a whale hold its breath?

01:14:19.929 --> 01:14:22.009
For about 20 minutes.

01:14:22.265 --> 01:14:25.465
- So we gotta beat the whale.
- Okay.

01:14:27.312 --> 01:14:29.632
We gotta beat the whale.

01:14:30.357 --> 01:14:31.637
Here you go.

01:14:31.858 --> 01:14:35.578
It's gonna be 20 minutes. You sure
you don't wanna go for an ice cream?

01:14:35.904 --> 01:14:38.784
Because you know
I'm gonna beat that whale.

01:14:39.324 --> 01:14:40.884
- Ready?
- Give me the count.

01:14:41.118 --> 01:14:43.278
Three, two, one, go!

01:15:01.097 --> 01:15:02.537
Sean?

01:15:05.393 --> 01:15:06.553
Sean?

01:15:09.564 --> 01:15:10.844
Sean.

01:15:17.406 --> 01:15:19.086
Have you seen...?

01:15:20.701 --> 01:15:25.021
I'm looking for my son. Have you
seen a boy in a red bathing suit?

01:15:26.874 --> 01:15:30.234
You seen my boy?
He's wearing a red bathing suit.

01:17:18.449 --> 01:17:23.169
Jad, we're ready to begin thermal scan
on all residences on North Powell.

01:17:24.414 --> 01:17:26.814
You must really like me, don't you?

01:17:27.083 --> 01:17:29.843
That's why you asked to partner
with me on this sortie.

01:17:30.128 --> 01:17:31.528
You're swell company.

01:17:31.754 --> 01:17:34.914
It's not that you don't trust me
to be alone with the chief, is it?

01:17:35.217 --> 01:17:37.377
That you think I might, you know,
futz with him?

01:17:37.635 --> 01:17:41.355
No, I just wanna watch him use your
body to sandblast another building.

01:17:41.682 --> 01:17:42.682
Evanna, go.

01:17:43.184 --> 01:17:46.464
I show 27 warm bodies.

01:17:46.770 --> 01:17:49.490
Roger that. Confirmed, 27 warm bodies.

01:17:49.774 --> 01:17:54.534
- Four spyders, one per floor?
- Let's do eight. I gotta eat.

01:18:10.128 --> 01:18:15.128
Residents of 931 Powell, this is
Officer Fletcher of D.C. Precrime.

01:18:15.509 --> 01:18:20.589
Under authority of P.C. section 6409, we
are deploying spyders into your complex.

01:18:22.016 --> 01:18:24.296
Mom, I'm scared.

01:18:24.602 --> 01:18:27.002
Mommy, I'm scared. Mommy.

01:18:27.271 --> 01:18:31.071
That's gonna scan you.
Keep your eyes open. Stay still.

01:18:31.401 --> 01:18:33.161
- It's okay.
- I don't like it.

01:18:33.403 --> 01:18:35.403
Stay still. Stay still.

01:18:59.012 --> 01:19:00.132
Come on!

01:19:00.347 --> 01:19:02.827
You stepped out on me
for the last time.

01:19:03.100 --> 01:19:04.620
I told you where I was.

01:19:04.852 --> 01:19:07.652
You're a no-good liar.
I know you was with that ho.

01:19:07.938 --> 01:19:09.498
You're lucky we...

01:19:13.778 --> 01:19:15.778
Leave me alone!

01:20:32.194 --> 01:20:33.674
We lost one.

01:20:34.071 --> 01:20:37.871
Roger that. Maybe it was
a cat jumping through a window.

01:20:38.450 --> 01:20:40.050
It's an awful big cat.

01:20:40.285 --> 01:20:41.605
Fletcher.

01:20:42.663 --> 01:20:44.543
I'll go check it out.

01:21:23.080 --> 01:21:26.320
They're crying their eyes out.
You terrified them.

01:21:26.625 --> 01:21:28.745
Keep your kids away from me.

01:21:44.185 --> 01:21:48.385
The big cat's back. What do you think?
A drunk, maybe can't wake up?

01:21:48.732 --> 01:21:51.252
Or a guy who doesn't want to get read.

01:21:51.526 --> 01:21:54.006
Folks, be quiet, go back inside.

01:22:04.999 --> 01:22:07.119
Be quiet and close the door.

01:22:14.258 --> 01:22:16.458
We got an ID. It's not him.

01:22:18.472 --> 01:22:21.232
- Standing down.
- Let's eat.

01:22:34.739 --> 01:22:37.419
Fletcher, take a look.

01:22:39.201 --> 01:22:42.281
There's four people in this room,
not three.

01:22:42.580 --> 01:22:45.940
Four? There's Anderton, Crow
and the man in sunglasses.

01:22:46.251 --> 01:22:49.411
The man in the sunglasses
is outside the window.

01:22:52.007 --> 01:22:56.487
There's also someone here
in the mirror.

01:22:57.345 --> 01:22:59.385
Definitely female.

01:22:59.932 --> 01:23:04.012
The Precrime program began in 2046
with a federal grant.

01:23:04.353 --> 01:23:09.393
And now, nine years later,
D.C. is the safest city in America.

01:23:09.776 --> 01:23:12.056
Why? Because Precrime works.

01:23:12.319 --> 01:23:15.439
Precrime has eliminated the need
for conventional detectives.

01:23:15.740 --> 01:23:20.380
What happens now is the verification
and protection of future victims.

01:23:20.745 --> 01:23:22.305
Can we see the Pre-Cogs?

01:23:22.539 --> 01:23:26.859
They have such a powerful gift,
they're kept in peaceful seclusion...

01:23:27.210 --> 01:23:29.130
...so as not to be distracted.

01:23:29.379 --> 01:23:33.699
This display should give you some idea
of what their daily life is like.

01:23:34.635 --> 01:23:38.315
The Pre-Cogs get over
8 million letters every year.

01:23:38.639 --> 01:23:40.559
That's more than Santa Claus gets.

01:23:40.808 --> 01:23:44.328
Each Pre-Cog has their own bedroom,
TV and weight room.

01:23:44.645 --> 01:23:46.725
It's wonderful to be a Pre-Cog.

01:24:12.174 --> 01:24:14.654
My mom's new boyfriend
came over again last night.

01:24:14.969 --> 01:24:17.129
He's just not very intelligent.

01:24:17.387 --> 01:24:22.987
My mom wouldn't let me eat upstairs.
I had to listen to him go on and on.

01:24:31.945 --> 01:24:33.625
Shit!

01:24:51.548 --> 01:24:54.268
Eye-dent: John Anderton.
Approved for entry.

01:24:58.472 --> 01:25:02.232
- Which I told her I'd be able to do.
I'm so good at taking care of you.

01:25:02.560 --> 01:25:06.920
But she thinks I'll be irresponsible.
It's ridiculous because...

01:25:09.609 --> 01:25:13.249
You can't be in here.
What are you doing here?

01:25:17.868 --> 01:25:20.588
Easy there, old-timer.
Who cleared you?

01:25:20.870 --> 01:25:22.830
- You're not allowed here.
- Listen, Wally.

01:25:23.081 --> 01:25:24.761
- Do I know you?
- I like you.

